that assumes that errors are independent and efficient Estimator, CÌƒEff in (17), that accounts
for the autocorrelated errors.
The reduced-rank estimators, as we may recall are the projections of these matrices to lower
dimensions with different weight matrices. These are as stated in Theorem 2.1, Theorem 3.1 and
the alternative calculations based on the Kroneckerâ€™s product structure. In the first alternative,
the weight matrix is taken to be, Î£Ìƒâˆ’1
